{"version":2,"kind":"Article","sha256":"be69bb7768f501c280793612ef17aa80b184033c4c55bb3a075d05cf83f72221","slug":"blog.2019.2019-10-13-rust-jupyter-governance","location":"/blog/2019/2019-10-13-rust-jupyter-governance.md","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"What would Rust-style governance look like in Jupyter?","tags":["governance"],"date":"2019-10-13","content_includes_title":false,"authors":[{"id":"chris","nameParsed":{"literal":"Chris Holdgraf","given":"Chris","family":"Holdgraf"},"name":"Chris Holdgraf","orcid":"0000-0002-2391-0678","affiliations":["affiliations-myst-generated-uid-0","affiliations-myst-generated-uid-1"],"url":"https://chrisholdgraf.com","github":"choldgraf","twitter":"choldgraf"}],"github":"https://github.com/choldgraf/choldgraf.github.io","affiliations":[{"name":"2i2c","url":"https://2i2c.org","id":"affiliations-myst-generated-uid-0"},{"name":"Project Jupyter","url":"https://jupyter.org","id":"affiliations-myst-generated-uid-1"}],"abbreviations":{"LF":"The Linux Foundation","JF":"The Jupyter Foundation","JEC":"Jupyter Executive Council","JFB":"The Jupyter Foundation Board","SSC":"Software Steering Council","OSPO":"Open Source Program Office"},"numbering":{"title":{"offset":2}},"source_url":"https://github.com/choldgraf/choldgraf.github.io/blob/main/blog/2019/2019-10-13-rust-jupyter-governance.md","edit_url":"https://github.com/choldgraf/choldgraf.github.io/edit/main/blog/2019/2019-10-13-rust-jupyter-governance.md","exports":[{"format":"md","filename":"2019-10-13-rust-jupyter-governance.md","url":"/build/2019-10-13-rust-jupy-bc03af4c46e6284ff4cb90277152729b.md"}]},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":14,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"As I’ve written about before, I ","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"qqeuvqNRXi"},{"type":"link","url":"https://chrisholdgraf.com/rust-governance","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"like Rust’s governance structure","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"rA2Tm8t6DN"}],"urlSource":"https://chrisholdgraf.com/rust-governance","key":"F22qXQDD4a"},{"type":"text","value":".\nI mean, who can’t get behind a community that\n","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"iUFr4Ht811"},{"type":"link","url":"https://www.rust-lang.org/governance","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"lists governance as a top-level page on its website","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"jVd7ZtxItf"}],"urlSource":"https://www.rust-lang.org/governance","key":"yDlgdAphVI"},{"type":"text","value":"?","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"HD36t1upcA"}],"key":"paIAKMuyff"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Jupyter is currently in the middle of\n","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"C6GaY6uFne"},{"type":"link","url":"https://discourse.jupyter.org/t/governance-office-hours-meeting-minutes/1480/26","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"figuring out the next phase of its governance structure","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"iVPXWbTY6j"}],"urlSource":"https://discourse.jupyter.org/t/governance-office-hours-meeting-minutes/1480/26","key":"DwbTQRnZHz"},{"type":"text","value":",\nand so I have been thinking about\nwhat this might look like. This post is a quick thought-experiment to explore what it’d mean\nto port over Rust’s governance directly into the Jupyter community.","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"i7WyWsu6Pl"}],"key":"jzaDtlxLjV"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":1},"end":{"line":22,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Note: I’m not an expert in Rust governance, so there are some assumptions made about its model\nbased on my outside perspective. Apologies if I miss any important details about the Rust model,\nbut this is mostly meant as as inspiration, not a report on Rust’s governance :-)","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":1},"end":{"line":22,"column":1}},"key":"rTrjkMaFQ1"}],"key":"l1PrmPFoAn"}],"key":"xfjqVzpRi0"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A quick recap of Rust’s governance structure","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"key":"wBNC72O9jF"}],"identifier":"a-quick-recap-of-rusts-governance-structure","label":"A quick recap of Rust’s governance structure","html_id":"a-quick-recap-of-rusts-governance-structure","implicit":true,"key":"CQq7z8GxYy"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":29,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"First off, how does Rust govern and organize itself? There are a few few\nkey pieces:","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":28,"column":1}},"key":"owlBwZeSJW"}],"key":"DudaDAnRV6"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1},"end":{"line":49,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1},"end":{"line":32,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Any significant changes to the codebase are proposed and discussed with a\n","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1},"end":{"line":31,"column":1}},"key":"UivcOZNJpr"},{"type":"link","url":"https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1},"end":{"line":31,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Request for Comments process","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1},"end":{"line":31,"column":1}},"key":"crsKt0Vb0p"}],"urlSource":"https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs","error":true,"key":"RqTAVPJ3mU"},{"type":"text","value":".","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":1},"end":{"line":31,"column":1}},"key":"bVds93k9bh"}],"key":"DVEoVf5p3F"}],"key":"tXAeonPhmz"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1},"end":{"line":35,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Rust community is broken down into topic-specific teams. Each has a particular\ndomain over which they make decisions. For a list of several teams, check out\nthe ","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1},"end":{"line":33,"column":1}},"key":"R6S3NtaapM"},{"type":"link","url":"https://www.rust-lang.org/governance/","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1},"end":{"line":33,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Rust governance page","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1},"end":{"line":33,"column":1}},"key":"Dzg1HWuchi"}],"urlSource":"https://www.rust-lang.org/governance/","key":"qlczTU2cx2"},{"type":"text","value":".","position":{"start":{"line":33,"column":1},"end":{"line":33,"column":1}},"key":"aRArp1DANU"}],"key":"Nv47qusYJd"}],"key":"T1ummxaI1i"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":36,"column":1},"end":{"line":37,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"There is also a core-team that cuts across topic teams and has representatives\nfrom each topic team, they discuss project-wide matters (but rarely).","position":{"start":{"line":36,"column":1},"end":{"line":36,"column":1}},"key":"wPfKnvBu3i"}],"key":"ZQcXVbaXJl"}],"key":"BLlufPl8qu"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":38,"column":1},"end":{"line":39,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"A new RFC is assigned a team, as well as a “shepherd” from that team. This person’s\njob is to move the RFC process forward, not to comment on or implement the RFC.","position":{"start":{"line":38,"column":1},"end":{"line":38,"column":1}},"key":"M5JK26Ikdd"}],"key":"bqIvC7xw0O"}],"key":"B1CiTVarfz"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":40,"column":1},"end":{"line":42,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"After a discussion period, all members of the sub-team must vote to enter\na Final Comment Period. This should happen when “enough information is presented in\nthe RFC to make a decision”. It triggers a week-long review window.","position":{"start":{"line":40,"column":1},"end":{"line":40,"column":1}},"key":"ThZZEYHbDt"}],"key":"bWyZoMFHnG"}],"key":"Gvlk2uWk5I"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":43,"column":1},"end":{"line":45,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"At the end of this window, a decision is made about what to do with the RFC. This\nis made by the members of the sub-team, who (I don’t think) have any strict decision-making\nrules, they can organize themselves in terms of decision-making.","position":{"start":{"line":43,"column":1},"end":{"line":43,"column":1}},"key":"hXiHftCm7j"}],"key":"pobCwMGrRV"}],"key":"EY6NniTvW6"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":46,"column":1},"end":{"line":49,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"If it is accepted, the RFC becomes “active” which is an invitation for people\nto work on implementing it.","position":{"start":{"line":46,"column":1},"end":{"line":46,"column":1}},"key":"OHZvLQ82yf"}],"key":"WxLbwi80Sv"}],"key":"fg7nSTg3bP"}],"key":"QjU5nhHdpG"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":50,"column":1},"end":{"line":50,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"What would this look like in Jupyter?","position":{"start":{"line":50,"column":1},"end":{"line":50,"column":1}},"key":"fLldFtWzsG"}],"identifier":"what-would-this-look-like-in-jupyter","label":"What would this look like in Jupyter?","html_id":"what-would-this-look-like-in-jupyter","implicit":true,"key":"CKpl7E8CPW"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":52,"column":1},"end":{"line":53,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Jupyter is a complex and multi-faceted community, but so is Rust, so let’s see\nwhat this decision-making structure would look like in the Jupyter community.","position":{"start":{"line":52,"column":1},"end":{"line":52,"column":1}},"key":"fYPxKrDhxn"}],"key":"Vlz77Cii1o"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":55,"column":1},"end":{"line":55,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"General decision-making principles and goals","position":{"start":{"line":55,"column":1},"end":{"line":55,"column":1}},"key":"AITXXSSXZt"}],"identifier":"general-decision-making-principles-and-goals","label":"General decision-making principles and goals","html_id":"general-decision-making-principles-and-goals","implicit":true,"key":"WUgD8IQ872"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":57,"column":1},"end":{"line":58,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"First off, we would adopt many of the same decision-making goals of the RFC\nprocess. Here are a few key ones as I understand it:","position":{"start":{"line":57,"column":1},"end":{"line":57,"column":1}},"key":"fEmeHeugYN"}],"key":"fUtfs7AYKc"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":60,"column":1},"end":{"line":70,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":60,"column":1},"end":{"line":61,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Be transparent - information about decision-making should be publicly available and\neasy to discover at any moment in time.","position":{"start":{"line":60,"column":1},"end":{"line":60,"column":1}},"key":"j7oYc58sun"}],"key":"kHdamPF1x6"}],"key":"rV0vlXhSLn"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":62,"column":1},"end":{"line":63,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Be inclusive - decision-making should strive to include many diverse voices in\nthe conversation.","position":{"start":{"line":62,"column":1},"end":{"line":62,"column":1}},"key":"baluJhQ9n9"}],"key":"t7DYCj8fXI"}],"key":"k3f84O8l4A"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":64,"column":1},"end":{"line":65,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Be informative - the goal of the RFC process is to surface relevant information\nand perspectives for making a decision.","position":{"start":{"line":64,"column":1},"end":{"line":64,"column":1}},"key":"ceEndHhkUC"}],"key":"bMSjOuMXzD"}],"key":"flsV2fokOG"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":66,"column":1},"end":{"line":67,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Be productive - the goal of the RFC process is to move ideas forward in the community.\nIt should achieve a net-positive in “energy spent” vs. “generated value to the community”.","position":{"start":{"line":66,"column":1},"end":{"line":66,"column":1}},"key":"anyCur05oA"}],"key":"aDZ59LKnQD"}],"key":"pf2lcV4XyD"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":68,"column":1},"end":{"line":70,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Be impactful - don’t use RFCs to bike-shed minor details, or implementation details for a PR.\nThey should be used for significant changes in a repository that require discussion at a high level.","position":{"start":{"line":68,"column":1},"end":{"line":68,"column":1}},"key":"rX1qYjRUgY"}],"key":"t7qyWZ4fMF"}],"key":"lLoTAnAPnK"}],"key":"Ikb5OR2SVv"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":71,"column":1},"end":{"line":71,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"An RFC in the Jupyter Community","position":{"start":{"line":71,"column":1},"end":{"line":71,"column":1}},"key":"HQwa0u8FoA"}],"identifier":"an-rfc-in-the-jupyter-community","label":"An RFC in the Jupyter Community","html_id":"an-rfc-in-the-jupyter-community","implicit":true,"key":"n4HQD32USN"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":73,"column":1},"end":{"line":74,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"First off, the mechanism for proposing, iterating on, and making decisions. In\nRust this is an RFC. in Jupyter, such a mechanism has already been proposed!","position":{"start":{"line":73,"column":1},"end":{"line":73,"column":1}},"key":"AlkY8xkjfa"}],"key":"zwepE12k67"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":76,"column":1},"end":{"line":79,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The ","position":{"start":{"line":76,"column":1},"end":{"line":76,"column":1}},"key":"rkm1qlKcvW"},{"type":"link","url":"https://github.com/jupyter/enhancement-proposals","position":{"start":{"line":76,"column":1},"end":{"line":76,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Jupyter Enhancement Proposals","position":{"start":{"line":76,"column":1},"end":{"line":76,"column":1}},"key":"RpIxlaPKbG"}],"urlSource":"https://github.com/jupyter/enhancement-proposals","error":true,"key":"Wk6JvlTD55"},{"type":"text","value":"\nhave been around for quite some time, though have never been codified into law official\ndecision-making and have become a bit stale. I suspect this is partially because it’s\nunclear what kind of “power” the JEP process has.","position":{"start":{"line":76,"column":1},"end":{"line":76,"column":1}},"key":"QIc1k3KYwi"}],"key":"sed4OclMAP"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":81,"column":1},"end":{"line":85,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Recently, ","position":{"start":{"line":81,"column":1},"end":{"line":81,"column":1}},"key":"vmkhVMEBoT"},{"type":"link","url":"https://github.com/captainsafia","position":{"start":{"line":81,"column":1},"end":{"line":81,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Safia","position":{"start":{"line":81,"column":1},"end":{"line":81,"column":1}},"key":"fpgOHJylie"}],"urlSource":"https://github.com/captainsafia","error":true,"key":"fRPlICvUsu"},{"type":"text","value":" kick-started a process to\n","position":{"start":{"line":81,"column":1},"end":{"line":81,"column":1}},"key":"HOz8k5Xj6y"},{"type":"link","url":"https://github.com/jupyter/enhancement-proposals/pull/29","position":{"start":{"line":81,"column":1},"end":{"line":81,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"revitalize the JEP process","position":{"start":{"line":81,"column":1},"end":{"line":81,"column":1}},"key":"jzWIJ1v1st"}],"urlSource":"https://github.com/jupyter/enhancement-proposals/pull/29","data":{"kind":"issue","org":"jupyter","repo":"enhancement-proposals","issue_number":"29"},"internal":false,"protocol":"github","key":"kCNdCtWRiE"},{"type":"text","value":", and\nthe proposed process is quite close to what the Rust community uses. I generally think\nthat this PR is a huge improvement, though for the sake of this thought experiment, I’m\njust going to directly port over my understanding of Rust into this blog post.","position":{"start":{"line":81,"column":1},"end":{"line":81,"column":1}},"key":"tX7FK2gNIT"}],"key":"TNIvnbpTI0"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":87,"column":1},"end":{"line":88,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Here’s how a Rust-like process could work in Jupyter. Since already have JEPs, I’ll\nreplace “RFC” with “JEP”.","position":{"start":{"line":87,"column":1},"end":{"line":87,"column":1}},"key":"LgijgKVxHc"}],"key":"tMOgOhuthx"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":90,"column":1},"end":{"line":109,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":90,"column":1},"end":{"line":90,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"We have a single “enhancement-proposals” repository where JEP discussion happens","position":{"start":{"line":90,"column":1},"end":{"line":90,"column":1}},"key":"v4trOx1WRE"}],"key":"z5uQEJqYDy"}],"key":"KdmEv8C90X"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"This repository has a template for new JEPs help people get started.","position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"key":"aWrgoNcQzc"}],"key":"dAvzNb9Eab"}],"key":"v3RThg1dO3"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":92,"column":1},"end":{"line":94,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"New JEPs begin with general conversations in the community. People get informal\nbuy-in and feedback through discussing in the ","position":{"start":{"line":92,"column":1},"end":{"line":92,"column":1}},"key":"Nt1Lgxp92E"},{"type":"link","url":"https://discourse.jupyter.org","position":{"start":{"line":92,"column":1},"end":{"line":92,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"community forum","position":{"start":{"line":92,"column":1},"end":{"line":92,"column":1}},"key":"icHsDJEbnF"}],"urlSource":"https://discourse.jupyter.org","key":"OVqdq5gbuJ"},{"type":"text","value":"\nor in GitHub repositories.","position":{"start":{"line":92,"column":1},"end":{"line":92,"column":1}},"key":"GOTe9zvTp6"}],"key":"ZraFGX6pYa"}],"key":"ddOCFexQ1R"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":95,"column":1},"end":{"line":96,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"If a person wants to make their JEP “official”, they fill in the JEP template and\nmake a pull-request to the repository.","position":{"start":{"line":95,"column":1},"end":{"line":95,"column":1}},"key":"lqzlLfqBdO"}],"key":"xxfgNpkwpz"}],"key":"hb8lmrzaGY"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":97,"column":1},"end":{"line":97,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"After an initial overview, a Jupyter team is assigned to the JEP.","position":{"start":{"line":97,"column":1},"end":{"line":97,"column":1}},"key":"VtXU8UDlS0"}],"key":"k4cdjhkV4S"}],"key":"DfRzl91IOK"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":98,"column":1},"end":{"line":98,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"That team then picks a shepherd (how the teams do this is up to them).","position":{"start":{"line":98,"column":1},"end":{"line":98,"column":1}},"key":"slDVmybBNb"}],"key":"jG2rMhOBrp"}],"key":"C8oAycstBv"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":99,"column":1},"end":{"line":100,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"The shepherd oversees a process of feedback, asks for input from others in the\ncommunity, and directs attention to the JEP on the listservs, community forum, etc.","position":{"start":{"line":99,"column":1},"end":{"line":99,"column":1}},"key":"jLGtXDKPuK"}],"key":"BF4O4QWoYe"}],"key":"jPMP5vqY7w"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":101,"column":1},"end":{"line":103,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"When the shepherd thinks that the JEP is ready for a decision, they ask their\nteam to vote on whether it should enter a “final review” phase. No more modifications\nshould be made to the JEP at this point.","position":{"start":{"line":101,"column":1},"end":{"line":101,"column":1}},"key":"BZluTok14e"}],"key":"TqvducoGFG"}],"key":"uhSUPfm4bP"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":104,"column":1},"end":{"line":106,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"This triggers a 7-day window for team members to review the JEP. At the\nend of the 7 days, the team votes (say, by a lazy consensus with 50% quorum)\non whether to accept the JEP.","position":{"start":{"line":104,"column":1},"end":{"line":104,"column":1}},"key":"DlaPnVCH92"}],"key":"MZwAzZpRVO"}],"key":"RMEC91qcIw"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":107,"column":1},"end":{"line":109,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"If accepted, the JEP enters an “active” state and pull-requests are welcome to\nimplement it.","position":{"start":{"line":107,"column":1},"end":{"line":107,"column":1}},"key":"KZDEVCWqSR"}],"key":"nxJ8WTq8rs"}],"key":"ptfhf3ubuy"}],"key":"SJzrPvstW7"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":110,"column":1},"end":{"line":110,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The teams and peronnel needed to manage this process","position":{"start":{"line":110,"column":1},"end":{"line":110,"column":1}},"key":"I28mvu7ncE"}],"identifier":"the-teams-and-peronnel-needed-to-manage-this-process","label":"The teams and peronnel needed to manage this process","html_id":"the-teams-and-peronnel-needed-to-manage-this-process","implicit":true,"key":"gvHxoIVy6x"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":112,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The JEP process is the ","position":{"start":{"line":112,"column":1},"end":{"line":112,"column":1}},"key":"MXnTiMYon0"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":112,"column":1},"end":{"line":112,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"mechanism","position":{"start":{"line":112,"column":1},"end":{"line":112,"column":1}},"key":"en2vim2NFT"}],"key":"APW1a7hc4Z"},{"type":"text","value":" by which decisions get made, but what\nare the groups tha