icially codify the JEP process","position":{"start":{"line":169,"column":1},"end":{"line":169,"column":1}},"key":"LhaS0UnkKY"}],"key":"Xi8ZtaXyNO"}],"key":"ZjINK6y87u"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":170,"column":1},"end":{"line":170,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"make some topic-based teams official, and get people to accept roles on those teams","position":{"start":{"line":170,"column":1},"end":{"line":170,"column":1}},"key":"vO4wjFibH2"}],"key":"YWpiA7xz7U"}],"key":"WbTqRAzia3"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":171,"column":1},"end":{"line":172,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"build some infrastructure to support the JEP process (e.g. a website to make them searchable\nand discoverable)","position":{"start":{"line":171,"column":1},"end":{"line":171,"column":1}},"key":"hyZ9tknNyg"}],"key":"WigtMh9bn1"}],"key":"NRsE0nmId7"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":173,"column":1},"end":{"line":176,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"re-work team processes to encourage them to follow the JEP process over time (I suspect this would\nbe the hardest thing to do)","position":{"start":{"line":173,"column":1},"end":{"line":173,"column":1}},"key":"wm8JTythkq"}],"key":"qdo2zd8JCi"}],"key":"Vr6rSOqin0"}],"key":"EaRJ6J6ZZ8"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":177,"column":1},"end":{"line":177,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"What’s the difference between Jupyter and Rust?","position":{"start":{"line":177,"column":1},"end":{"line":177,"column":1}},"key":"LrZ7MyHkh2"}],"identifier":"whats-the-difference-between-jupyter-and-rust","label":"What’s the difference between Jupyter and Rust?","html_id":"whats-the-difference-between-jupyter-and-rust","implicit":true,"key":"Mnc96Er1Nn"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":179,"column":1},"end":{"line":181,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Finally, while it’s interesting to port one community’s governance model directly onto another,\nthere are difference between the Jupyter and Rust projects, both technical and social ones.\nHere are a few differences I can think of that might have an impact on how this model would work.","position":{"start":{"line":179,"column":1},"end":{"line":179,"column":1}},"key":"mqDJi2iakF"}],"key":"VaANH0IDwR"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":183,"column":1},"end":{"line":196,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":183,"column":1},"end":{"line":187,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":183,"column":1},"end":{"line":183,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Jupyter evolves fairly quickly","position":{"start":{"line":183,"column":1},"end":{"line":183,"column":1}},"key":"OL4leF0KAR"}],"key":"MyS26FSNX2"},{"type":"text","value":" - Whether it is JupyterLab development, the growth of new\nprotocols or deployments in the JupyterHub stack, or extensions of Jupyter tools for new\nuse-cases, Jupyter seems to move fairly quickly. The RFC (or JEP) model is one that intentionally\nslows things down, so perhaps we’d need to be more picky about when to follow such a model\nvs. when to allow codebases to grow more quickly.","position":{"start":{"line":183,"column":1},"end":{"line":183,"column":1}},"key":"ugb0Oa4Q7X"}],"key":"tPW5TweQNy"}],"key":"G3lKoaJU5t"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":188,"column":1},"end":{"line":191,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":188,"column":1},"end":{"line":188,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Jupyter doesn’t have a process like this already","position":{"start":{"line":188,"column":1},"end":{"line":188,"colu